    {
      "text": "Parasol Stars: The Story of Bubble Bobble III (パラソルスター) is a 1991 platform game developed and published by Taito for the TurboGrafx-16. It is a sequel to 1987's Rainbow Islands, and the third game in the Bubble Bobble series. The game was ported by Ocean Software to the Amiga, Atari ST, Game Boy and Nintendo Entertainment System (with the NES port released under the title Parasol Stars: Rainbow Islands II). On July 11, 2024, the game was digitally re-released for the PlayStation 4, PlayStation 5, Xbox One, Xbox Series X/S, Nintendo Switch, and Windows. On April 19, 2026, the game got another release for modern consoles as part of a bundle with Spica Adventure under the name Parasol Superstars.",
